9:
Technically, we are meeting with a
noble who governs land adjacent to
the borderlands—not anyone
holding central seats of power.
14:
Still, this is an enormous step in the
right direction.
18:
It was all thanks to Sarliha. Her ties
to the royal family and the
priesthood laid the groundwork.
20:
In addition, we have donated food
and technology from Qualia City as
a sign of goodwill.
24:
Are you certain it was all right to do
so? Should such technology fall into
the wrong hands...
28:
That will not be a problem. Love and
her associates made sure of it.
30:
The technology they donated is
meant to be used by children in
their world, so it is all perfectly safe.
32:
However, it was more than enough
to impress the noble.
37:
Hah! That doesn't surprise me. In the
desert, even baby tech would seem
like magic!
46:
So, what's on the agenda with that
stodgy old coot?
53:
Before our alliance is finalized, we
would like to proceed with signing
an off-the-record non-aggression
treaty.
59:
Uh... Are these negotiations gonna
happen out here? In the middle of
the desert?
63:
Our associate does not wish to draw
attention from the main forces of
the kingdom.
65:
I see Lady Sarliha's compassion
knows no bounds. To think she
would associate with this rabble...
67:
But, there is something to be gained
here. I have no idea how you got
your hands on such advanced
technology, but—
70:
Stop right there. I understand your
need for protection, but this is
ridiculous.
73:
Silence, rat. Do you realize how
much I risk just by attending this
meeting? One or two guards is
nothing!
77: Count again, bub. Look behind you.
83:
That flag... It belongs to one of the
most militant noble factions in the
desert!
86:
Th-this can't be! How did word of
our meeting get out?! If they find out
I'm here, I'm done for!
89:
I suppose this wasn't some
elaborate setup after all...
92:
Of course not, you dolt! Ngh, with
their numbers, we don't stand a
chance...
95: Negative. This is far from over.
99:
How unfortunate... It appears the
path ahead will not be an easy one.
114:
Hurry! We must escape while we still
can!
117:
And how do you propose we do that,
exactly?! The rest of their troops will
close in on us!
120: Fear not. We have a way.
130:
Hey, you got that peace treaty
signed, so it was worth it!
135:
The look on that noble's face was
rich. He almost pissed himself back
there.
140:
At least there was a silver lining. He
learned firsthand how capable the
alliance is.
145:
We certainly have the advantage of
being able to retreat quickly and to
a safe haven.
147:
In the event that the kingdom
attacks, we have instructed the
people of the borderlands to use our
network of World Flippers to escape.
152:
Access to the World Flippers is
restricted, so the kingdom's forces
will not be able to follow them.
156:
If the situation worsens, we will
consider having the people of the
borderlands migrate to another
world to avoid conflict.
161:
Migrate... Ah, you mean you'll copy
Lilith's plan and bring those people
to the Garden of the Sprites?
166:
Wouldn't it be easier to just have 'em
pack up and move right now?
170:
Perhaps. But there are still many
who do not wish to leave their
homes.
178:
Those militant factions won't make it
easy to unite your world.
182:
True. But I do not believe the worst
will come to pass. I still have hope.
184:
Slowly but surely, the kingdom is
changing from within.
193:
Of course, we cannot expect a
resolution to come at once.
197:
The night is long... And it will last until
the people are able to forget their
pain and put the past behind them.
201:
But I believe that, someday, we will
find our peace.
209:
But remember, even you have limits.
You should take a well-deserved
rest for the time being.
213:
I apologize, but I cannot rest just yet.
There is something very important I
must do first.
218:
Right. We'll be waiting for you back
in Starview.
222: Rashid... I have missed you so.
225:
I wanted to tell you... that we did it.
Today, we took our first step towards
the peace you always hoped for.
228:
Your last wish has became my own
dream.
230:
So please... give me strength. Watch
over me as you always have.
233:
Until the new dawn we envisioned
rises upon this land!
242:
...I know now what I must do. If all
you wish to bring upon this world is
ruin...
246:
Then I will not allow you to stand in
the way of our dream!
249:
I vow to crush the stars and shatter
the night!
